28/04/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul says his government intends to improve relations with all its neighbours, without discrimination.
"We want to show that a Muslim country can be together with an open, transparent, democratic and modern world," Gul told the Diplomacy Journalists Association General Assembly on Sunday (27 April).
He added that peace, security and stability in the region would benefit all and that the Turkish government would work towards achieving those ends.
(Anadolu Agency - 27/04/03)
